The method takes three parameters: `firstWord`, `secondWord`, and `targetWord`.
`firstWord`, `secondWord`, and `targetWord` are non-null strings.
`firstWord` and `secondWord` contain only alphabetical characters.
`targetWord` contains only alphabetical characters.
`firstWord` and `secondWord` represent numerical values when converted to integers.
`targetWord` represents a numerical value when converted to an integer.
